name: ethanedione, di-2-furanyl-, dioxime
Reason: 1,2-furanyl groups, when connected to a dioxime ring, significantly increase the melting point due to the ability to enhance π-π interactions and overall molecular rigidity. Each furanyl group may contribute around +30 to +50°C. The dioxime ring itself also contributes to the melting point due to its rigidity and potential hydrogen bonding, estimated at around +20 to +30°C.
